## Context
PRs #702 and #705 added GPU-vectorized and CPU-parallel null model
permutation testing.  The code is merged and validated on real data
(3h → 7min), but the documentation doesn't reflect the new pipeline
capabilities.

## Actions
1. [done, PR #706] Update `.claude/rules/architecture.md` Phase 2 rules to mention
   null model acceleration (GPU for S2/S1, precomputed TF-IDF for L1,
   joblib for citation methods, NJOBS knob).
2. [done, PR #706] Update `docs/handoff-padme-divergence.md` to include null model
   parallelism and the NJOBS override example for `make -jN`.
3. [deferred] Add a paragraph to the technical report methods section
   describing the permutation test implementation. `content/_includes/structural-breaks.md`
   still describes the obsolete KMeans+JS pipeline — a permutation paragraph
   there would sit beside incoherent legacy prose. Belongs with the
   structural-breaks.md rewrite (tracked in 0034/0040).

## Test
`grep -c 'n.jobs\|NJOBS\|GPU.*null\|parallel.*permut\|_permutation_accel' .claude/rules/architecture.md` returns ≥ 3.
`grep -c 'NJOBS\|null-model\|_permutation_accel' docs/handoff-padme-divergence.md` returns ≥ 3.

## Exit criteria
Architecture.md mentions the three acceleration strategies (GPU batched matmul, precomputed TF-IDF, joblib) and the NJOBS / -j interaction.
Handoff doc covers null-model parallelism with a concrete `make -jN NJOBS=...` example.
Technical-report paragraph tracked as follow-on under the structural-breaks.md rewrite.
